After months of mindset work and research, I finally made the jump and yes, it was hard and it took time, but I wake up every morning feeling excited about my days and possibilities of what I could make happen that day, with people whom I love ğŸ’—
What I realized in my research was that thereâ€™s been a lack of knowledge sharing, focused support and camaraderie for folks who are transitioning to freelance, especially for strategists.
But due to fear of stability, money and self-belief, Iâ€™ve been pushing it off for the longest time.

Freelancing is a vehicle and opportunity to make a living on our own terms.  Iâ€™ve had a desire to go independent for a while - create projects with people I believe in, work with companies I want to contribute to and truly own the time that I have this lifetime.
I believe we all deserve to thrive and live in alignment with how we want to live our lives.

The standard of a 9-5 (or rather in some industries, 9-9??) was created to put us in boxes and extract as much productivity as possible to benefit the corporation. It was, at its roots,  designed without considerations of our intersectionalities and desires.

Corporate America is not made for everyone to thrive. The past two years have pushed a lot of us to see the injustices of our systems much more clearly, prompted us to rethink how we live our lives and solidify the impact we want to make in this world.
